HEADWORD: Poetical
<hw>Po*et"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>po⟦eum⟧ticus</ets>,
Gr. <?/: cf. F. <ets>po⟦eacute⟧tiquee</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of
or pertaining to poetry; suitable for poetry, or for writing poetry;
<as>as, <ex>poetic</ex> talent, theme, work, sentiments</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Expressed in metrical form; exhibiting the
imaginative or the rhythmical quality of poetry; <as>as, a
<ex>poetical</ex> composition; <ex>poetical</ex> prose.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Poetic license</b></col>. <cd>See <er>License</er>,
